In article <CMK5qA.2wD@news.direct.net>, Kim Allen <kallen@indirect.com> wrote:

>
>Just to bring up a small point. A patent, just like a tradename, has to 
>be defended to stay valid. If RSA posted a FAQ giving the impression that 
>they will allow use of the software AND they don't defend the patent 
>(i.e. through legal action) then they will lose the right to the patent 
>I found this out from some people whom this happen to. Or go ask a patent 
>lawyer

Not a small point, but a very important one.

In this case, RSA/PKP have been vigorous in pursuing infringers. Since to
date every infringer has "caved" the matter has never come to court. However
there is a very good paper trail that they've defended their patent when
aware of infringement.

David


